Venice of the North: Theorizing Change in Hökarängen -- tMAPPINGS -- tIntegrating Amsterdam Noord -- tCultural Assets in Schöneweide -- tThe Normalization of Thamesmead: Part B -- tSouth of the South in Venice of the North: Mapping Change in Hökarängen -- tOther Narratives: Reading Sub/Urban Theory Differently -- tContributing Authors -- tAcknowledgements0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aUrbanizing Suburbia considers three current and related processes underway in global cities: the hyper-gentrification of inner cities, the financialization of housing, and the structural changes occurring in the outer city. Rocketing housing prices have displaced residents from inner cities and created a rent gap in outer cities. Increasingly, municipalities, developers, and displaced residents search for opportunities in the suburban belts. Changes in demographics, densities, live/work ratios, and tenures are remaking outer cities, rendering them less and less suburban. The book examines these changes by looking at four key European cities: Amsterdam, Berlin, London, and Stockholm. It is a first attempt at understanding the three processes discussed here within one comprehensive explanatory framework.  aUrbanizing Suburbia erforscht die Beziehung zwischen drei aktuellen Prozessen in globalen Städten: Hyper-Gentrifizierung der Innenstädte, Finanzialisierung des Wohnens und strukturelle Veränderungen in Vororten. Die explodierenden Wohnungspreise in Großstädten haben zu einer enormen Abwanderung von Einwohner*innen aus den Innenstädten geführt, von denen sich viele in den Speckgürteln niedergelassen haben. Dieser demografische Wandel führt in Verbindung mit den spezifischen Sanierungsstrategien der Kommunen zu einer Neustrukturierung der Vorstädte. Die Publikation untersucht diese Veränderungen am Beispiel von vier europäischen Großstädten: Amsterdam, Berlin, London und Stockholm. Es ist ein erster Versuch, diese drei Prozesse innerhalb eines umfassenden Rahmens zu betrachten.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aAmsterdam Noord. 4aBerlin housing. 4aPost-Olympic East-London. 4aStockholm Middle Ring. 4aThamesmead. 4ahypergentrification. 4asuburbia. 4asuper-gentrification.1 aAalbers, Manuel B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernstock, Penny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernt, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBunnik, Paco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, Juliet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDel Ben, Berta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aExo Adams, Ross, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFanni, Maryam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGennburg, Katalin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHellström, Elof, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaminer, Tahl , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKaminer, Tahl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKockelkorn, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrivý, Maroš, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMa, Leonard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMa, Leonard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMack, Jennifer S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatz, Karin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, Timothy, econtributor.